<paragraph blockId="12.[151,978,495,524]" box="[151,978,495,524]" pageId="12" pageNumber="23">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,978,495,524]" fontSize="12" level="1" pageId="12" pageNumber="23" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,978,495,524]" pageId="12" pageNumber="23">
<taxonomicName authority="Coste &amp; Ricard 1980" authorityName="Coste &amp; Ricard" authorityYear="1980" box="[151,740,495,524]" class="Monogenea" family="Capsalidae" genus="Nitzschia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Capsalidea" pageId="12" pageNumber="23" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="draveillensis">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,447,495,523]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="23">Nitzschia draveillensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Coste, M. &amp; Ricard, M." box="[455,740,495,524]" pageId="12" pageNumber="23" pagination="187 - 212" refId="ref17607" refString="Coste, M. &amp; Ricard, M. (1980) Observation en microscopie photonique de quelques Nitzschia nouvelles ou interessantes dont la striation est a la limite du pouvoir de resolution. Cryptogamie: Algologie 3: 187 - 212." type="journal article" year="1980">Coste &amp; Ricard 1980</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[757,906,495,524]" captionStart="FIGURE 42–51" captionStartId="13.[151,244,1377,1398]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,197,1356]" captionTargetId="figure-205@13.[151,1436,197,1356]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 42–51. Nitzschia dravaillensis, strain LCR-S:37:3, CHR618409. Scales: Fig. 42, 10 µm; Fig. 49, 5 µm (use for Figs 43–49); Fig. 50, 1 µm; Fig. 51, 0.5 µm. Fig. 42. Live cells viewed by LM. Figs 43–49. Cleaned frustules viewed by LM, showing size variation, and median fibulae visible in 43. Fig. 50. SEM of cleaned frustule showing raphe canals on opposite margins, and median fibulae. Fig. 51. TEM of cleaned frustule showing median fibulae and raphe with central termini." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5062012" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5062012/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="23">Figs 42–51</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[919,969,495,524]" captionStart="FIGURE 162" captionStartId="28.[151,244,1590,1611]" captionTargetBox="[154,1433,626,1529]" captionTargetId="figure-383@28.[151,1436,617,1569]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 162. Bayesian phylogenies of Nitzschia strains from the Styx River, for rbcL (left) and 18S rDNA (right). Support numbers above branches are Bayesian posterior probabilities / Maximum Parsimony bootstrap values. Scale bar = 0.1 subsitutions/site. See text for substitution models and description of data sets." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5062040" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5062040/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="23">162</figureCitation>
)
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,572,755]" pageId="12" pageNumber="23">
Frustules fusiform with extended rostrate poles, 47.0–63.0 µm long, 
<quantity box="[887,1010,572,595]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.95" metricValueMax="4.5" metricValueMin="3.4" pageId="12" pageNumber="23" unit="mm" value="3.95" valueMax="4.5" valueMin="3.4">3.4–4.5 µm</quantity>
wide in valve view; sometimes slightly constricted at midpoint at one or both margins. Living cells containing 2 plate-like parietal chloroplasts, one towards each pole (
<figureCitation box="[419,503,636,659]" captionStart="FIGURE 42–51" captionStartId="13.[151,244,1377,1398]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,197,1356]" captionTargetId="figure-205@13.[151,1436,197,1356]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 42–51. Nitzschia dravaillensis, strain LCR-S:37:3, CHR618409. Scales: Fig. 42, 10 µm; Fig. 49, 5 µm (use for Figs 43–49); Fig. 50, 1 µm; Fig. 51, 0.5 µm. Fig. 42. Live cells viewed by LM. Figs 43–49. Cleaned frustules viewed by LM, showing size variation, and median fibulae visible in 43. Fig. 50. SEM of cleaned frustule showing raphe canals on opposite margins, and median fibulae. Fig. 51. TEM of cleaned frustule showing median fibulae and raphe with central termini." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5062012" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5062012/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="23">Fig. 42</figureCitation>
). Striae very fine, transverse, 
<quantity box="[854,952,636,659]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7907" metricValueMax="1.8288" metricValueMin="1.7526" pageId="12" pageNumber="23" unit="in" value="70.5" valueMax="72.0" valueMin="69.0">69–72 in</quantity>
<quantity box="[963,1039,636,659]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="23" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 µm</quantity>
, not visible in LM. Raphe system marginal, fibulate, 21–23 fibulae in 
<quantity box="[596,670,668,691]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="23" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 µm</quantity>
, but with two median fibulae more widely spaced; raphe on opposite margins of the two valves. Central raphe endings occurring between median fibulae (
<figureCitation box="[1104,1182,700,723]" captionStart="FIGURE 42–51" captionStartId="13.[151,244,1377,1398]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,197,1356]" captionTargetId="figure-205@13.[151,1436,197,1356]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 42–51. Nitzschia dravaillensis, strain LCR-S:37:3, CHR618409. Scales: Fig. 42, 10 µm; Fig. 49, 5 µm (use for Figs 43–49); Fig. 50, 1 µm; Fig. 51, 0.5 µm. Fig. 42. Live cells viewed by LM. Figs 43–49. Cleaned frustules viewed by LM, showing size variation, and median fibulae visible in 43. Fig. 50. SEM of cleaned frustule showing raphe canals on opposite margins, and median fibulae. Fig. 51. TEM of cleaned frustule showing median fibulae and raphe with central termini." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5062012" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5062012/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="23">Fig. 51</figureCitation>
, visualised in TEM; not discerned either in LM or SEM).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
